main event: Multiple objects were spotted in the sky over Kent, Tacoma, and McChord AFB, Washington on March 26-27, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were described as looking like a transparent kite or a bi-plane, and were estimated to be the size of a large aircraft.
The objects were sighted at high altitudes, moving in a westerly direction, and appeared to be drifting slowly without any noticeable maneuvers.
Witnesses used binoculars and a telescope to observe the objects, but were unable to discern many details due to the high altitude.
Weather conditions at the time of the sightings were clear, with no wind or cloud cover reported.
The sightings lasted for approximately 20-30 minutes before the objects faded from view as the sky grew darker.
sighted object: one to three transparent, kite-like or bi-plane-shaped objects
